Thanathorn Juangroongruangkit, the leader of Thailand's progressive Future Forward Party, on Saturday denied charges of sedition filed against him by the ruling military government. His anti-junta movement came third in last month's elections after campaigning on a pledge to oust army chief Prayuth Chan-oocha, who has kept a tight grip on power since a 2014 coup. A guilty conviction could cost Thanathorn his seat in parliament, delivering a blow to the alliance of democratic opposition parties trying to form a government. Read more: Thailand on its way back to democracy? Send  Facebook   Twitter   google+   Whatsapp   Tumblr   linkedin   stumble   Digg   reddit   Newsvine Permalink https://p.dw.com/p/3G12D What do the charges involve? nm/tj (AP, Reuters, AFP)